-- Changsha Zoomlion Heavy Says Company Planning Public Listing in Hong Kong
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-06T22:53:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/changsha-zoomlion-heavy-says-company-planning-public-listing-in-hong-kong.html

          
          
             Changsha Zoomlion Heavy Industry
Science and Technology Development Co. plans to list shares in
Hong Kong, the company said in a statement to Shenzhen’s stock
exchange.  
 The company’s board of directors has approved the plan,
according to the statement. Shares sold publicly in Hong Kong
may account for as much as 15 percent of Zoomlion’s outstanding
shares after the listing, according to the statement.  
 Zoomlion also said in a separate statement that first-half
net income may rise 50 percent to 100 percent from a year
earlier to 1.63 billion yuan ($240 million) to 2.17 billion
yuan.  
